description: Now With 80 Pages And More New Stories! In 'Archie Loves Betty: Freshman Year-The First Semester' Part 4, Archie makes a startling realization about his career, while Betty discovers a new mission. Meanwhile, in 'Archie Loves Veronica: The Trial of Reggie Mantle' Part 4' Reggie stands trial! But for what? And 'Jinx' continues in 'Li'l Jinx Grows Up!' Part 4 by award-winning creator J. Torres and artist Rick Burchett.

This issue features pants wetting humor from Max Cannon (Red Meat), Eric M Esquival, Gerrad McConnell, and Steven L Frank! Amazing artwork by Matt Hebb, Shawn Van Briesen, and Bill McKay! Shops that order this top-selling title are selling out!
name: Student Bodies; Braindead Youth; Zombie-ing Camp

description: Teachers run amok on campus as students and faculty switch places for "Role Reversal Day"! Then, Chuck's exaggerated caricatures for the school newspaper are "Drawing Attention," but not the way they were meant to! Can Chuck clear up the creative confusion?
name: Role Reversal Day / Drawing Attention

description: Nothing good ever comes out of cloning-- just ask Archie! In an attempt to juggle dates with both Betty and Veronica, Archie gets himself cloned and finds double the trouble in "The Clone Caper"! Then, in "Pilot Program," Mr. Weatherbee loves the peaceful halls of Riverdale High, especially when... a helicopter flies through the hallways?! Plus Chuck finds a "Draw Flaw" when some people don't quite appreciate his portraits of them.
name: The Clone Caper / Pilot Program / Draw Flaw

description: 'Little Archie/Tiny Titans.' The world of Archie Comics and DC Comics collide in the complete collection of the three-part Little Archie/Tiny Titans crossover! Pandemonium and brand-new friendships abound as a simple laundry switch leads to adventures with Robin, Beast Boy, Josie and the Pussycats, Sabrina the Teenage Witch, and Archie & friends! Plus, is Miss Grundy related to Solomon Grundy?
name: Tiny Titans / Little Archie and His Pals

description: In “The Junkman Cometh,” lightning strikes Dilton’s failed invention of a robotic brain. Suddenly it begins to transform with other inventions into a giant robot! Then, in “Don’t Mind Me” Dilton falls for the new student. As he plans on how to introduce himself, he plays out how Archie, Reggie and Moose would do it, when all he needs to do is be himself. Finally, in “Whack Attack,” the gang takes on the challenge of paddle ball, but the best player may surprise you!
name: The Junkman Cometh / Don't Mind Me / Whack Attack

description: Riverdale High is in for a culinary treat! In “Cafeteria Cook Showdown,” Ms. Beazley has been selected to compete in the Regional Cafeteria Cook-off…and wait to you see what she makes! Next, “The Gig” finds the Archies competing to be in a movie about a struggling band. But the film is being shot in Alaska!
name: Cafeteria Cook Showdown / The Gig

description: XIII thought he knew who he was, but now he's not sure anymore. He could be Kelly Brian, an IRA terrorist tracking CIA...
name: Secret Defense

description:
Two determined journalists are investigating the recent events, mainly President Sheridan's broadcasted judgement. One of them commits a "very appropiate" suicide and the other flees to Europe, but his investigation is not finished... 
 
This issue clarifies the past of all the main characters, except for XIII, that still has to deal with his condition...
name: The XIII Mystery: L'Enquete

description:
XIII still is in Central America, backed up by Waly Sheridan. General Carrington still wants to get to the bottom of all this conspiracy. He wants the truth, his daughter Kim didn't died in vain. 
Number I has been identified and XIII knows now who he is, but this hasn't finished yet...
name: Le Jugement

description: At last, XIII learn his family's past, who his real father is and why Jonathan MacLane had to pass himself as his father...
name: Trois Montres d'Argent

description: Minerco, a mysterious and powerful enterprise, is trying to prove that XIII is El Cascador, a revolutionary hero executed three years ago. XIII finds the widow of El Cascador, waiting for her execution. She is the only one who can tell XIII the truth...
name: El Cascador

description: XIII and Jones go to Central America to find Betty Barnowsky. There, Padre Jacinto, some sort of a guerilla priest, tells XIII that he has a wife, and she is about to be executed...
name: Pour Maria

description:
La Mangouste (The Mongoose) has managed to escape Bluebanks prison. President Sheridan (ex-President Sheridan's brother) offers a job to XIII: find who is number I, the person responsible for his brother's assassination. After learning that La Mangouste has escaped, XIII accepts.
  
XIII must now find Kelly Rowland, but finds a lot more than he expected... 
 
It was originally supposed to be the last issue.
name: Treize contre Un

description:
Sheriff Quinn and "La Mangouste" are chasing XIII and Jones, but they miss once more. XIII leaves Jones with Judith at Greenfalls, so she can recover from her wounds, but she's going to have a visit from Dwight Rigby's men. She manages to escape and Rigby goes after XIII.
 
Rigby arrives to Zeke's house, where XIII found documents about Jason Fly's past. They will both learn at last Fly's true identity...
name: La Nuit du 3 Aout

description:
XIII is looking for clues about Jason Fly's past, since it could be his true identity. After meeting Jason's father, his investigations leads him to an old man, Zacharias Hattaway, who seems to recognice XIII's voice as Jason's.  
 
"La Mangouste" and his men are looking for XIII everywhere, but they find Jones, more than twice...
name: Le Dossier Jason Fly

description:
During the funeral of Henry Sheridan, there is an assassination attempt on his son Wally, Senator. The shooter fails and gets killed by a sniper. Admiral Heideger, Secretary of Defense Donnely, Judge Longman and General Carrington are arrested as accessories to the attack, conspiracy and treason. Documents implicating them were found at the house of the shooter. Other documents link them to Jason Fly and implicate them in the assassination of President William Sheridan.

It looks like the "tattooed group" wants them away so they can take over the nation during Operation "Rouge Total"...
name: Rouge Total

description:
Under the name Ross Tanner, XIII is sent among the S.P.A.D.S. (SPecial Assault & Destroying Sections) to a mission somewhere in South America.
Colonel Amos discovers that the file of Ross Tanner was created by General Carrington as a false clue. Jones knew this but she's gone with the S.P.A.D.S..
Amos also finds out that Steve Rowland is buried under the name Jason Fly. The judge Allenby is part of conspiracy and has number VI tattoed in his chest. Allenby is killed, and his killer is shot down by Kim Rowland.
Amos will learn at last the true story of Steve Rowland, and how he was married to Kim, and how she is the daughter of General Carrington.
name: S.P.A.D.S.

description:
Colonel Amos meets General Carrington and tells him how he might be able to prove that XIII has had some sort of advanced facial surgery, wich could prove that he really is Rowland. Amos asks to search for everybody who has being trained for the special forces. There is only one file missing: Ross Tanner, who's only particular characteristic is claustrophobia. 
 
XIII is still kept in Plain Rock Penitenciary. Jones finds her way in but XIII already has his escape plan. Along with another prisoner he's trying to get out through narrow pipes, and he doesn't seem to get any claustrophobia...
name: Toutes les Larmes de l'Enfer

description:
XIII is in a military base, looking for information about Steve Rowland, the man he believes he was, but Rowland is dead. General Carrington tells him how he was trained be a member of the SPADS, a US army special forces. Carrington also proves with photos that XIII really is Steve Rowland.
XIII goes to Rowland's house. His rich father is now disabled and married with his nurse, Felicity. His oncle Matt runs the family exploitation. Everybody's surprised to see him, but XIII doesn't remember anyone. Matt and Felicity are lovers and are planning to kill Steve's father to inherit his fortune.  
 
XIII, in his personal investigation, enlarges the photo that Carrington gave him and sees an indian in a lake, next to a house. He is determined to go to that house, but it's not going to be easy...
name: La Ou Va l'Indien...

description:
A fisherman finds a wounded man at the beach and takes him home. He has the number XIII tatooed and suffers amnesia. 

One day he finds the couple who rescued him dead, and two men trying to kill him. He kills one of them and finds a photo in wich he appears with an unknown woman. He then starts to look for clues, but it seems everybody wants him dead...
name: Le Jour du Soleil Noir

description:
XIII is getting ready to leave Mexico. Irina, Jessica and Executor's killers are getting close. The head of the Mob and Felicity have found him too. At last, all the answers... 
 
This issue features more than 150 characters who have appeared throughout the volume!
name: Le Dernier Round

description: Who is XIII? Jason Fly, an american journalist, or Kelly Brian, an irish terrorist?
name: La Version Irlandaise

description: XIII and Jones are still after the treasure of Maximilien. The are wanted for the assassination of the President. They find a place to hide in Mexico, from where they plan to condemn Frank Giordino, the head of the National Security Agency...
name: L'Or de Maximilien

description: XIII and Jones go after Maximilien's treasure...
name: Operation Montecristo

description: XIII is still accused of beinf an IRA terrorist, and is almost killed by the National Security Agency. He gets rid of them, but only to be chased by a criminal organisation called Executor instead. Again, everybody seem to want him dead, including Jessica, who by the way looks like X-men's Rogue...
name: Lachez les Chiens!

description: Kasumi is a special girl–and not just because she’s a super-cute high schooler with a heart of gold. She has a major secret: She can turn invisible when she holds her breath. But when she transfers to an elite private school, it gets harder to keep her superpowers secret, especially when she catches the eye of the handsome student-body president, Ryuuki, and becomes the target of his number one fan, mean girl extraordinaire Reina. Can Kasumi keep hiding who she really is?
name: The Invisible Girl

description: Karin is your lovable girl-next-door type–if the girl next door also happens to be a goddess! Karin has a magic ring that gives her the power to do anything she’d like. What she’d like most, though, is to live happily ever after with Kazune, the boy of her dreams. Magic brought Kazune to her, but it also has a way of complicating things. It’s not easy to be a goddess and a girl in love!
name: Goddess of Love!

description: Sachiko is wildly attracted to the quiet, cool Akihiko, the “Four-Eyed Prince.” But now they’ve become siblings by marriage–and must live under the same roof, as brother and sister! And if that isn’t bad enough, it turns out that Akihiko is hiding a surprise behind those nerdy glasses.
name: Secret Crush

description: Life isn’t fair! Sachiko has a huge crush on her new stepbrother, Akihiko, a cute boy whose glasses make him even hotter, but he shows no interest in her. When she meets a group of hard-core fans of eyeglasses, she learns about the dreamy “Four-Eyed Kiss.” Can she convince Akihiko to give her one?
name: Geek Love

description: Sachiko remains hopelessly and one-sidedly in love with her stepbrother, Akira. But now she must compete with an overeager guy to be Akira’s assistant--not to mention contending with a spoiled little princess from Karuizawa and a ghost with a particular fondness for glasses!
name: Four-Eyed Free-For-All

description: Those suffering from this peculiar condition, according to Zetsubou-sensei, blame themselves for everything that goes on around them. But as Zetsubou-sensei explores this affliction, he realizes that he himself is a victim! Luckily, the sensei has a foolproof plan for putting an end to Delusional Self-Blaming Disorder--which happens to involve a long rope dangling from a tree. Could this be the end of Zetsubou-sensei?
name: Delusional Self-Blaming Disorder

volume.name: Sayonara, Zetsubou-Sensei: The Power Of Negative Thinking

description:
Hello, Kokona here. So I just started dating my first boyfriend. His name is Renji-kun, and he’s handsome and talented and supersmart. But now that we’re going out, what are we supposed to actually do? Can someone please give me some advice? I’m totally clueless about love!

Includes special extras after the story!
name: Relationships 101
Bob Morane et la Vallee des Crotales
Bob Morane et le Mystere de la Zone "Z"
Bob Morane contre La Terreur Verte
Bob Morane et le Collier de Civa
Bob Morane et les Tours de Cristal
Bob Morane et le Secret de l'Antarctique
Bob Morane et l'Oiseau de Feu

description: A special one-shot paying homage to Dwayne McDuffie and the world of Milestone Media, with tribute material from Milestone co-founder Denys Cowan and other Milestone alumni.
name: I am the Future

description: Now that Karin has found all of the Three Noble Gods, it’s time to join forces to save the future! But when Karin overhears Kazune saying he doesn’t want her around, she’s afraid their plans are already doomed. Will Karin’s dream of saving the day end before it even begins?
name: Fumbled Future

description: The world is a lonely place for Naoto and Naoya, brothers with amazing psychic powers that set them apart from humanity. Their parents cast them out–and had them imprisoned in an exploitative research center. But after they make a daring escape from the institution, Naoya has a psychic vision of an even greater threat: a deadly plague that threatens the entire world!
name: Save Me

description: Karin has lost her memory, and there’s no telling how much damage the bad guys can do while she’s unable to transform. The only way to get Karin’s memory back is for Jin to use Professor Kirihiko Karasuma’s power. But can he do that without turning to the dark side?
name: Who Am I?

description:
As Doctor Who reaches its mid-season climax, DWM talks exclusively to actress ALEX KINGSTON about keeping the incredible secret of the true identity of her back-to-front alter-ego, River Song...

“Right up until the reveal, people are enjoying trying to guess. Is she really on the Doctor’s side? Or is there something more to her? Is she actually not such a good person? Even once we know who River is, I don’t think we’ve lost her potential for adventure.”

ALSO THIS ISSUE:

AND BABY MAKES FOUR!
DWM takes a peak at what we can expect from STEVEN MOFFAT’s game-changing episode, A Good Man Goes to War. Where is Amy? Who is the Eye Patch Lady? What is River’s secret? All will be revealed... or will it...?

HAVE YOU MET MY WIFE? SURANNE JONES talks exclusively to DWM about what it was like to play Idris – the TARDIS given physical form, in the amazing episode, THE DOCTOR’S WIFE, written by the award-winning NEIL GAIMAN.

GOODBYE SARAH JANE... Following the sad news of the death of ELISABETH SLADEN,DWM commemorates the much-loved actress and the character of Sarah Jane Smith that she created. Doctor Who’s commander-in-chief, STEVEN MOFFAT reflects on the enduring popularity of the character in his latest PRODUCTION NOTES; and former Doctor Whoshowrunner and executive producer of The Sarah Jane Adventures, RUSSELL T DAVIES shares his fond memories of working with Elisabeth. Plus, an obituary and a selection of the many letters received from readers.

SEEING DOUBLE!
DWM braved the biting cold to report on the disturbing two-part adventure, THE REBEL FLESH/THE ALMOST PEOPLE and was able to talk exclusively to the cast and crew, including author MATTHEW GRAHAM, actor RAQUEL CASSIDY, and director JULIAN SIMPSON.

GENTELMEN ADVENTURERS... From 1977’s The Talons of Weng-Chiang to their own series of adventures on audio, actors CHRISTOPHER BENJAMIN and TREVOR BAXTER talk exclusively to DWM about playing Victorian detectives Jago and Litefoot.

END OF AN ERA As the 60s draw to a close, so too does the tenure of the Second Doctor as COUNTDOWN TO 50 reaches Series Six which introduced both UNIT and the Time Lords to Doctor Who mythology.

RUNNING OUT OF TIME! Amy and the Doctor confront nuns with guns when they land inside an abandoned alien vessel where time is the enemy in APOTHEOSIS, the first part of a new comic strip adventure by Jonathan Morris with art by Dan McDaid.

RETURN OF AN OLD ACQUAINTANCE... THE TIME TEAM take a trip to the subterranean layer of tycoon and extraterrestrial collector, Henry van Statten to see the Doctor confronting an old enemy. Will DALEK be to their taste?

GONE TO PIECES... Summoned by the White Guardian, the Doctor is charged with the mission of finding the six segments of the Key to Time and the Time Lady Romana is assigned to help him in his task. FACT OF FICTION examines THE RIBOS OPERATION from 1978, and tracks down some fascinating facts about the adventure.

OF GODS AND MEN... Should the Doctor be an all-powerful, god-like being or just a clever chap with an inquisitive streak? TOBY HADOKE and JOHNNY CANDON take sides and fight their respective corners in A BATTLE OF WITS...

PLUS! All the latest official news, previews, reviews, competitions, more madness from the Watcher, another prize-winning crossword, and much, much more!

AND! A FREE giant-size, double-sided poster!
name: Birthshock!

description:
Hello, Kokona here. Renji-kun was about to kiss me for the first time, but then he stopped! Did I do something wrong? I’m so embarrassed. I thought boys were supposed to like kissing! How long will I have to wait for his next sweet attempt? And how am I going to practice my technique!?

Includes special extras after the story!
name: Kiss Off?

description: With the appearance of stronger Seeds of Chaos, Kazune decides to see what he can learn in the future. But time travel is not so easy, and if something goes wrong, Karin may never see Kazune again! Can he keep his promise to come back to her?
name: Years Apart

description: Michiru has left his friends after learning what the future holds for him. Karin wants to bring him back, and the new school play is her chance! Will playing one of the Three Musketeers remind Michiru how important it is to be one of the Three Noble Gods?
name: One For All

description: Karin has learned in a dream that the future is much worse than anyone thinks, and now she’s the only one who can save those she loves. She can’t bring herself to share the shattering truth, but how can she face the possibility of this nightmare alone?
name: A Dark Future

description:
Kakeru thought he was an ordinary guy destined for a boring life. But now his life is one big adventure. A group of psychic teens has come to him for help: They’ve had a vision that he’s part of their destiny. Can they believe in Kakeru...even if he doesn’t believe in himself?

Chapter Titles

  • Case 9: Conclusion
  • Case 10: Disappearance
  • Case 11: Giant
  • Case 12: Decision
name: Believe In Me

description: Kasumi has a simple plan for high school: make new friends and fall in love. She’s already got the friends, her faithful fanboy Otaku Ken and the kindhearted Maiko. And she just might be in love with Ryuuki, the hottest guy in school. But fate has something a little more magical in store for Kasumi. Ryuuki seems to know her secret–and hints that he has a few secrets of his own. Kasumi unexpectedly becomes the object of another boy’s affections when the alluring “Feather Prince” declares his love for her, and then she discovers the secret behind her magical powers...from the mysterious being who holds the key to her amazing destiny!
name: Magical Girl

description: While Aeon Clock arrives to save Kazu and Emily from a mysterious Storm Rider, another enemy attacks the members of Genesis with such force that even the Air Treck elite, the Keepers of Regalia, are on high alert. The evil unknown riders have put everyone in great danger, but who are these menaces, and what do they want?
name: Mystery Threat
Um Brilhante Nada Falso
Em Busca Do Ouro
O Holandês Voador
À la recherche de la Triste Marie
Les bébêtes qui démontent
Colecionando Confusão
O Sapo E A Princesa
Voa, Pombinho, Voa
Gato Preto Dá O Quê?

description:
Kakeru’s life changed when he met the girl of his dreams, the beautiful Ayano. But falling in love with her came with strings attached: Ayano is a gifted psychic whose talents have made her the target of a group of supervillains. She’s also helped Kakeru discover his own extraordinary destiny–because Kakeru may be the most powerful psychic of all...

Chapter Titles

  • Case 13: Love
  • Case 14: Jealousy
  • Case 15: Inhumanity
  • Case 16: Crack
  • Case 17: Progress
name: Secret Superpowers

description: Ikki is close to realizing his dream of becoming the Wind Keeper, and his achievements have won him a mysterious admirer: the beautiful Kururu, who claims that fate decrees she must serve the Wind Keeper. Who is this gorgeous girl–and could she be Ikki’s destiny?
name: King of the Wind

description: Storm Shadow and Zartan invade The Pit! One can't be killed and the other can't be seen! At the same time, General Hawk and Dial-Tone are being stalked by an army of killers in our nation's capital. They're on the run with no one to trust. The Cobra Civil War is just getting started!
name: Cobra Civil War Part 4

description: Attuma the Barbarian, enemy of Namor, the Sub-Mariner -- it was prophesized long ago that he would one day conquer Atlantis. But now, powered by a Hammer of the Serpent, he will become one of the Worthy -- those who will conquer the world.
name: The Worthy: Attuma

description:
Hath the world known anyone so noble as Hogun? So dashing as Fandral? So ,er, great as the mighty Volstagg? Hath the world ever known anything like the Warriors Three? The answer is 'no,' and that's probably a good thing - for the tectonic plates of Midgard most likely could not withstand such ah might.

But lo, an evil is brewing down in the depths of Hel that neither man nor God is prepared for. When an ancient monster is let loose on the world, only the Warriors Three are able to rise to the challenge! From the bestselling comics writer Bill Willingham (Fables) and breakout artist Neil Edwards (FANTASTIC FOUR) comes a tale of such magnitude the Marvel Universe has never seen!

Collecting WARRIORS THREE #1-4 - plus a classic saga of the Warriors Three and a monster of greener color from 1968's TALES TO ASTONISH #101 and INCREDIBLE HULK #102 by Stan Lee, Gary Friedrich and Marie Severin.
name: TPB
Aquele Banho

description: Cassie and Vlad go undercover at a Washington State high school to investigate the mysterious disappearance of several students. Hilarity and mayhem ensue as Cassie joins the cheerleading squad and Vlad gets recruited for the football team! If you read the title of the comic, you might be able to figure out what is going on at this particular high school, but is it really so crystal clear? Covers by Tim Seeley, Mike DeBalfo, Dominic Marco, and Benjamin Glendenning.
name: Hack/Slash Meets Zombies Vs Cheerleaders

description: Nathan Never moves into the mining base Artic 3 , North Pole, under the false identity of Thomas Ripley , to investigate the traffic of Polycloridric Euridal , a powerful amphetamine that can triple the performance of the miners . The top executives of the company , starting with the director of the base , Richard Shepard , a re involved in the traffic
name: Terrore sotto zero

description: The passengers of a shuttle, Dr. Alan Byrne and the young June , are kidnapped and delivered on Hell 's Island , an island on which access is prohibited due to a dangerous virus that has infected the people , making them horrible mutants . Nathan Never is sent to free the two prisoners and bring them back within forty-eight hours, before being infected as well.
name: La zona proibita
